de.humatic.dsj

Class JavaSourceGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Canvas
        • de.humatic.dsj.DSFiltergraph
          • de.humatic.dsj.DSGraph
            • de.humatic.dsj.JavaSourceGraph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public class JavaSourceGraph
extends DSGraph
    JavaSourceGraph subclasses DSGraph to simplify the setup of rendering Java graphics into DirectShow contexts. It is constructed via DSGraph's static createJavaSourceGraph(..) method.
    This creates a video only graph, so when rendering to wmv or asf, pass a video only profile.
    A similiar setup can be constructed by using DSGraph's insertJavaSourceFilter(...) method and building the rest of the graph in application code. When %renderFile is null on construction, this will run display-only.
